<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 EARTHQUAKE PREPARED: Securing Your Home, Protecting Your Family by Joel Leach 
(Studio 4 Productions, P.O. Box 465, Northridge, Calif. 91328: $8.95, plus 
$2.24 postage & handling; 63 pp., illustrated, paperback original). It's not 
too late to prepare for the inevitable Next One, and Leach provides clear, 
easy-to-follow instructions and diagrams on how to secure furniture, appliances 
and bric-a-brac. (He even includes a diagram of the gas valve that's invariably 
mentioned in earthquake safety literature.) One problem he fails to address: 
How to fit all the stuff an emergency kit is supposed to contain in the average 
car. 
</P>
