<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBERT LEVINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Jawbox, "For Your Own Special Sweetheart," Atlantic. On its major-label 
debut, this Washington D.C.-based punk band continues to do what it does best: 
churn out frantic, tension-filled guitar rock.The most obvious comparison would 
be to fellow D.C. punks Fugazi, but Jawbox's fury is more melodic -- so much so 
that the guitars on such songs as "Savory" almost shimmer when they're not 
cranking out distorted bursts of noise. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). A rating of five stars (a classic) is 
reserved for retrospective albums. ROBERT LEVINE 
