<P>
JUST THE FACTS; MOTORCYCLE MEANDERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mere mention of the word motorcyclist is apt to conjure up an image of a 
leather-clad loner roaring off into the sunset.However, it's more than likely 
that he or she is bound for one of America's top vacation spots, according to a 
poll of 1,600 enthusiasts that identified motorcyclists' top 10 destinations in 
1993. They are, in order a preference: 
</P>
<P>
 1) Grand Canyon 
</P>
<P>
 2) Sturgis, S.D. (site of an annual rally) 
</P>
<P>
 3) St. Louis, Mo. 
</P>
<P>
 4) Denver, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 5) San Francisco 
</P>
<P>
 6) Rapid City, S.D. 
</P>
<P>
 7) Las Vegas 
</P>
<P>
 8) Milwaukee, Wis. 
</P>
<P>
 9) Albuquerque, N. M. 
</P>
<P>
