<P>
A-PLANT SHUTS DOWN AS PRECAUTIONARY MOVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A nuclear power plant shut down Friday after an electrical relay failure. A 
low-level emergency was declared for about four hours. 
</P>
<P>
 There was no release of radioactivity and no threat to the public or plant 
workers, said the Omaha Public Power District, which owns and operates the 
plant. 
