 * Senior Health and Peer Counseling sponsors free crisis counseling to 
Westside residents who need help dealing with the emotional impact of the 
Northridge quake. Counselors are available from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. at the Ken 
Edwards Center, 1527 4th St. in Santa Monica. Counselors are also available to 
make home visits. Appointment or information: (310) 576-2550. 
