COMMUNITY NEWS: SANTA MONICA: SAINT JOHN'S RESUMES OUTPATIENT SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saint John's Hospital and Health Care Center on Monday will reopen outpatient 
services damaged in the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Outpatient services in the Joyce Eisenberg Keefer Breast Center and Saint 
John's Heart Institute will be available along with imaging, radiation oncology 
and nuclear medicine services in the south wing. 
</P>
<P>
 Administrators have said the badly damaged north wing will be razed and 
rebuilt. The south wing is expected to fully reopen by August and the undamaged 
west wing, where minor outpatient surgeries are performed, has been operating 
since the quake. 
</P>
<P>
 The damage forced the city's largest employer to lay off 1,750 of its 2,000 
employees. Administrators plan to meet today with workers to address the future 
of the hospital and possible rehiring. 
</P>
<P>
