<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUR MORTGAGE; HOW TO AVOID RIP-OFFS AFTER NATURAL DISASTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A two-hour panel discussion entitled "How to Avoid Being Ripped Off Following 
a Natural Disaster" will be held at 6:30 p.m. Thursday in the Venice Senior 
High School auditorium, 13000 Venice Blvd., Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Speaking will be representatives of the city attorney's office, the county 
Department of Consumer Affairs and local contractors. Admission is free. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021394-0146 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 013019 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
February 13, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Real Estate; Part K; Page 5; Column 1; Real Estate Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
