<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARRY MORRISON; MANAGED L.A. DOWNTOWN BUSINESS MEN'S ASSN. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harry Morrison, 80, general manager of the Los Angeles Downtown Business Men's 
Assn. from 1946 until 1954, and a civic booster who, through the Chamber of 
Commerce, helped spark the explosion of freeways in the post-World War II 
years. Morrison, who also headed the new International Downtown Executives 
Assn. in 1954, left municipal service work that year to become general manager 
of the Western Oil and Gas Assn., retiring in 1975. In Palmdale on Feb. 3. 
</P>
