<P>
HANNIBAL BACK DOING JOB FOR 49ERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL McLEOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rod Hannibal spent the first month of the Big West Conference season in the 
dog house, but since he regained his starting job six games ago, the senior 
forward has been a key for Long Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 He made a key three-point basket with less than 90 seconds remaining Saturday 
night as the 49ers defeated San Jose State, 73-66, before 1,593 in the campus 
gym. 
</P>
<P>
 San Jose State (12-9, 8-5), which suffered only its second loss in its last 
nine games, led, 33-24, near the end of the first half and by six points at 
intermission. 
</P>
<P>
 But Hannibal, who was benched in early January for academic violations, scored 
five points as Long Beach (12-7, 6-5) took a 44-42 lead. The score remained 
close the rest of the way; the lead changed hands or the score was tied another 
12 times. 
</P>
<P>
 A turnaround jumper by Terrance O'Kelley with 3:18 to go gave Long Beach the 
lead for good, 63-62. Then Hannibal, who scored 17 points, launched the 
three-point basket. 
</P>
<P>
 "That was the back-breaker," San Jose State Coach Stan Morrison said of 
Hannibal's three-pointer. PAUL McLEOD 
</P>
