<HEADLINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH STATE BEATS SAN JOSE STATE, 73-66 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL McLEOD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rod Hannibal spent the first month of th Big West Conference season in the dog 
house, but since he regained his starting job six games ago, the senior forward 
has been a key for Long Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 He made a key three-point basket with less than a 90 seconds remaining 
Saturday night as the 49ers defeated San Jose State, 73-66, before 1,593 in the 
campus gym. 
</P>
<P>
 San Jose State (12-9, 8-5), which suffered only its second loss in its last 
nine games, led, 33-24, near the end of the first half and by six points at 
intermission. 
</P>
<P>
 But Hannibal, who was benched in early January for academic violations, scored 
five points as Long Beach (12-7, 6-5) took a 44-42 lead. The score remained 
close the rest of the way;the lead changed hands or the score was tied another 
12 times. 
</P>
<P>
 A turnaround jumper by Terrance O'Kelley with 3:18 to go gave Long Beach the 
lead for good, 63-62. Then Hannibal, who scored 17 points, launched the 
three-point basket. 
</P>
<P>
 "That was the back-breaker," San Jose State Coach Stan Morrison said of 
Hannibal's three-pointer. 
</P>
<P>
 Two free throws each by Hannibal and O'Kelley helped Long Beach keep the 
Spartans at bay down the stretch. O'Kelley had 20 points. 
</P>
