<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge lost to Southern Utah, 81-71, Saturday night in a 
nonconference basketball game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors (5-16) led, 39-31, at halftime and were within 62-60 late in the 
game, but Southern Utah's Andy Ward made nine of 10 free throws during the 
final four minutes to put the game away. Ward finished with 18 points for the 
Thunderbirds (13-9). 
</P>
