<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; MASTER'S POSTS 13TH VICTORY IN ROW, 92-57 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior Andy Thompson scored 22 points and freshman Mike Penberthy came off the 
bench to add 20 as The Master's College defeated Christian Heritage, 92-57, in 
a nonconference men's basketball game Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the 13th in a row for the Mustangs (24-3), their 21st in the 
last 22 games, and set a school record for victories in a season. Master's was 
23-12 during the 1991-92 season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs made 37 of 64 shots, led by Penberthy's eight-for-nine effort. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 86, Whittier 57 -- Derrick Clark had 20 points and 11 rebounds 
for Cal Lutheran in the Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference 
game at Whittier. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the fifth in the row for the Kingsmen (20-1, 9-1), equaling 
the school record for wins in a season, set last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 79, West L.A. 59 -- Mike Wright scored 20 points on nine-of-10 
shooting to lead the Vaqueros (14-13, 5-3) in a Western State Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 85, Oxnard 74 -- Sean Martin scored 23 points and Paul Foster had 20 
points and 12 rebounds for the Raiders (22-8, 4-3) in a WSC game at Oxnard. 
Danny Alexander also scored 20 for Moorpark. Wendell Nunnery scored 18 points 
for Oxnard (12-15, 3-3). COLLEGE BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 8, Cerritos 1 -- R.J. Fenolio went four for four with two RBIs as 
Canyons (2-0) won at Cerritos (4-1). Fenolio had a double in the ninth inning 
when Canyons broke open a 3-1 game with five runs. Bobby Cowan (1-0) pitched 
seven innings, allowing one earned run and five hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 10, LACC 5 -- Eric Cole continued his hot hitting as he went 
three for four with two triples and three RBIs. The Marauders' third baseman is 
eight for nine with a home run, double, four triples and seven RBIs in Antelope 
Valley's last two games. 
</P>
<P>
 Kings River 8, Glendale 4 -- Despite Ed Gillis' three hits, Glendale lost in 
the semifinals of the Kings River tournament. Gillis, a sophomore second 
baseman, had two doubles and a single. 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 4-5, Cal Baptist 1-4 -- Pitchers Chris Beck and Ryan Dowhouer 
highlighted Master's first two victories of the season in an NAIA District 3 
doubleheader in Newhall. Beck (1-1) allowed one hit over eight innings in the 
opener. Dowhouer threw a five-hitter in the second game. 
</P>
<P>
 Master's (2-4, 2-0) won the first game with four runs in the eighth. Tony 
MacCaughtry homered and went three for four in the second game. Jeff Tomlinson 
had four hits in the doubleheader. 
</P>
