</P>
<P>
 Santa Paula 44, Moorpark 42 -- Moorpark's Mike McKenzie stole the ball from 
Manuel Escamilla with 15 seconds left, but Escamilla stole it back when 
McKenzie stopped to set up for the shot. 
</P>
<P>
 Escamilla, who had a game-high 21 points, then banked in a six-foot jump shot 
at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was played to determine which Frontier League team would receive the 
higher seeding in the Southern Section Division IV playoffs. Santa Paula (15-9) 
and Moorpark (12-12) each finished 4-4 in league play. HIGH SCHOOL WRESTLING 
