<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; EDISON EARNS A REST AFTER BEATING OCEAN VIEW, 75-58 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER BARZILAI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After playing four games in six days, the Edison boys' basketball team finally 
can rest, knowing it has secured a spot in the Southern Section playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers beat Ocean View, 75-58, in the Sunset League fourth-place playoff 
game Saturday, 24 hours after beating Servite in an emotional double-overtime 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just wanted to sleep good tonight," Edison Coach Larry Hirst said. "Now we 
don't have to worry about a committee deciding whether or not we get in." 
</P>
<P>
 Edison had to come back from a 17-point deficit with 13 minutes remaining to 
send Friday's game to overtime. But Saturday, the Chargers took an 8-0 lead and 
never trailed. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were really afraid that we'd be tired emotionally and physically," Hirst 
said. "We tried to substitute some in the first half and give our starters a 
rest, but they did a real good job and responded real well." 
</P>
<P>
 The Seahawks put together a 6-0 run to end the first half and closed to 27-25. 
But Edison pulled away midway through the third quarter, taking a 46-39 lead 
into the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Edison then put the game away with a 15-7 run. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Johnson led Ocean View with a game-high 24 points, Darrell Adams 
finished with 20 points and Jason Sist had 13 for Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 In Olympic League boys' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 66, Brethren Christian 42 -- Matt Herr scored 16 points for 
Calvary Chapel (13-13, 7-5), which earned fourth place and a spot in the IV-A 
playoffs. Third-place Brethren Christian finished the regular season 16-9 and 
8-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove League individual wrestling championships: 
</P>
<P>
 Four Santiago wrestlers win -- Santiago had four champions, including 
heavyweight Matt Eckert, the most valuable wrestler in the high weight 
division. PETER BARZILAI 
</P>
</TEXT>
