<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECTED CHLORINE LEAK FORCES EVACUATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A possible leak in a 150-gallon chlorine tank at a water department pumping 
station led to the evacuation of four homes in Camarillo late Saturday 
afternoon, a Ventura County Fire Department spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The department sent a hazardous material team to the site at 4:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Traffic was directed around the pumping house at Los Posas Road and Ponderosa 
Drive until about 7 p.m., when the hazardous materials team was able to shut 
off the valve, a Ventura County Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 No injuries were reported. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
