<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE INJURED AS TILES TOPPLE AT HOME DEPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three family members, including a 6-year-old boy, were taken to area hospitals 
Saturday after they were injured by boxed ceiling tiles that tipped over at a 
home improvement warehouse, firefighters said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident took place about 4:30 p.m. at Home Depot at 601 Placentia Ave., 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 A woman believed to be in her 60s was taken to the UCI Medical Center in 
Orange for her injuries, while a 6-year-old boy believed to be her grandson was 
taken to St. Jude Medical Center in Fullerton for minor injuries. A man 
believed to be related to the other victims also was taken to St. Jude for 
treatment for minor injuries, firefighters said. Home Depot officials declined 
to comment about the accident. 
</P>
