<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTHQUAKE: THE ROAD TO RECOVERY; 4 MILES OF SIMI FREEWAY WILL REOPEN MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MYRON LEVIN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four miles of the Simi Valley Freeway closed by last month's Northridge 
earthquake will reopen in time for the Monday morning commute, Caltrans 
officials have announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The freeway will reopen between the San Diego and Foothill freeways, along 
with most of the connectors linking the Simi Valley with the Foothill, Golden 
State and San Diego freeways. 
</P>
<P>
 However, ramps connecting the southbound Golden State to the eastbound Simi 
Valley, and linking the northbound and southbound San Diego to the westbound 
Simi Valley freeway will continue to be closed, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Caltrans on Saturday also announced that the Golden State Freeway between 
Lyons Avenue and Roxford Street, both northbound and southbound, will be closed 
for quake-related bridge repairs periodically during the next several days. 
</P>
<P>
 From 11:30 p.m. Monday until 5 a.m. Tuesday, and again from 11:30 p.m. Tuesday 
until 5 a.m. Wednesday, southbound auto traffic will have to exit at Lyons and 
detour along San Fernando Road to the Antelope Valley Freeway before rejoining 
the Golden State at Roxford. Depending on progress of the work, the same 
closure may be in effect from late Wednesday night to early Thursday, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 During the hours of the closure, southbound truck traffic will have to exit at 
California 138 and detour to the Antelope Valley Freeway before rejoining the 
Golden State at Roxford. Trucks traveling south from Bakersfield may be better 
off taking California 58 to the Antelope Valley Freeway and take the Golden 
State Freeway at Roxford, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The northbound closure will affect the same stretch of the Golden State during 
the same hours, but is scheduled to begin Wednesday night. Northbound autos 
will join the Antelope Valley Freeway at Roxford and take San Fernando Road 
back to the Golden State at Lyons. At Roxford, northbound trucks will take the 
Antelope Valley Freeway to California 138 or 58. 
</P>
</TEXT>
