<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE SEEK ATTACKERS WHO SHOT 2 IN A CROWD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police here are searching for several people who shot into a crowd outside a 
dance party late Friday night, injuring two teen-agers. 
</P>
<P>
 A 19-year-old Santa Ana man and a 17-year-old Anaheim youth received gunshot 
wounds to the upper body and were taken to a local hospital, said Newport Beach 
Police Sgt. Andy Gonis. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonis said the pair's wounds are not life-threatening, but both youths will 
probably remain in the hospital for a couple of days. Police did not release 
the victims' names or the name of the hospital.  
</P>
<P>
 An altercation took place about 11:30 p.m. at the Plaza de Cafes, a food court 
at 4881 Birch St. near John Wayne Airport that occasionally opens as an 
after-hours music hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonis said the fight broke out inside the auditorium-size building as several 
hundred Orange County teen-agers and young adults were dancing. The fight, 
involving several dozen people, then moved outside, where multiple shots from a 
handgun and a shotgun were fired, Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We probably had multiple suspects firing randomly at a crowd of people 
without provocation, and that is pretty consistent with gang-related shootings 
that have happened elsewhere in the county," Gonis said. "That is our suspicion 
at this time." 
</P>
<P>
 Police are looking for a Latino man, approximately 18 years old, with a 
mustache, and a black sedan, possibly a Ford Thunderbird, that may have been 
involved. Descriptions of the others were not available. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about the shooting is asked to call the Newport Beach 
Police Department at (800) 550-NBPD. 
</P>
