<P>
'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The snow storm that paralyzed much of the East Coast of the United States the 
last two days resulted in additional Olympics coverage for CBS. 
</P>
<P>
 When the Georgetown-Providence college basketball game the network had planned 
to telecast Saturday was postponed because the Hoyas were unable to fly out of 
Washington, CBS substituted two hours of the Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
 CBS had live coverage of portions of the Norway-Russia and Austria-Germany 
hockey games, along with preview reports on figure skating and skiing. STEVEN 
HERBERT 
</P>
</TEXT>
