<P>
'94 WINTER OLYMPICS / LILLEHAMMER; NOTEBOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Defending Olympic champion George Hackl of Germany drew the No. 1 starting 
assignment for today's first of two heats in men's luge. 
</P>
<P>
 Wendel Suckow and Duncan Kennedy of the United States will start 10th and 
12th, respectively, with the top tier of 12 reversing order for the second 
heat.The final two heats will be held Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Hackl, who was second in the 1988 Olympics, had an erratic World Cup campaign, 
finishing third behind Markus Prock of Austria and Kennedy. He also lost the 
European championship to Prock on his home track in Konigssee, Germany. 
</P>
<P>
 Cammy Myler, who later carried the U.S. flag in the opening ceremony, finished 
second to Susi Erdmann of Germany in women's practice runs for the second day 
in a row. The women begin competition Tuesday. ROSS NEWHAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
