</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Officials from the Immigration and Naturalization Service will renew permanent 
residency green cards Tuesday at the One Stop Immigration and Education Center, 
3600 Whittier Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Green cards issued before 1978 must be exchanged for a new identification 
card. These may be renewed Downtown at the Federal Building, which offers the 
service during business hours Monday through Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone interested in visiting One Stop for Tuesday's processing should call 
Juanita Quintero to reserve a space. 
</P>
