<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EAST LOS ANGELES; 2 RECEIVE HONORS AT VALENTINE GALA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Centro Mental Health and Human Services Corp. honored businesswoman 
Priscilla Lizarraga and broadcaster Henry Alfaro with El Corazon de la Vida 
Awards on Thursday at its second annual Gala Valentine's Ball. 
</P>
<P>
 "Throughout the years, there have been people who have helped not only El 
Centro, but the community," said Genevieve Gomez Lopez, director of community 
outreach services and the event coordinator. 
</P>
<P>
 Lizarraga, president of the Daikonia Associates catering business, is a member 
of the auxiliary group Friends of El Centro and has helped refurbish the 
children's room at the main facility. 
</P>
<P>
 Alfaro has hosted El Centro fund-raisers over the last 10 years, Lopez said. 
</P>
