COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: PICO-UNION; REDEVELOPMENT ADVISORY PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Redevelopment goals and objectives and the impact of the recent earthquake 
will be the focus of upcoming meetings of the two citizen advisory committees 
working with the Community Redevelopment Agency. 
</P>
<P>
 The Project Area Committees serve as the formal means through which a 
cross-section of residents participate in revitalization and redevelopment with 
the redevelopment agency. 
</P>
<P>
 The 155-acre Pico-Union 1 project area is bounded by Olympic Boulevard on the 
north, the Harbor Freeway on the east, the Santa Monica Freeway on the south, 
and Union and Burlington avenues on the west. The 227-acre Pico-Union 2 project 
area is bounded by Olympic Boulevard on the north, Union and Burlington avenues 
on the east, Hoover Street on the west and the Santa Monica Freeway on the 
south.  
</P>
<P>
 The Pico-Union 2 meeting is Monday; the Pico-Union 1 meeting is Feb. 22. Both 
begin at 7 p.m. at the redevelopment agency's Pico-Union site office, 1316 S. 
Union Ave. 
</P>
