<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH-CENTRAL; PENNY DRIVE TO HELP YOUTH TRIP TO AFRICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teen Post Inc. is sponsoring a penny drive to raise funds for its third annual 
trip to Africa for local youths. 
</P>
<P>
 The proceeds from the drive, which began earlier this month, will help pay for 
a two-week tour of Egypt scheduled for July, said Georgia Hunt, director of the 
South-Central Teen Post. 
</P>
<P>
 As many as 10 youths from Teen Post's Cultural Education Project will be 
selected for the trip, Hunt said. Each participant is expected to contribute 
about $2,500 toward air fare and lodging, and Teen Post will provide additional 
monies, Hunt said. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, started in 1989, focuses on providing a cultural and educational 
vacation for youths ages 9 to 17. 
</P>
<P>
 In past years, the program has taken students to Ghana and the Ivory Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 The Watts Credit Union is among local businesses supporting the program by 
collecting pennies. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're interested in (this program) because we're interested in all community 
projects that add to the quality of life here," said Jim Taylor, chief 
executive officer of the Watts Credit Union. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're encouraging our members to support this program." 
</P>
<P>
 Teen Post Inc. provides field trips and mentoring for local youths in 
Chinatown, Venice, Pueblo del Rio and South-Central. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 232-2411. 
</P>
</TEXT>
