<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCCER; MULES KICK THE DEMS FOR LEAGUE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ENRIQUE LAVIN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Victor Arana's goal gave Wilson a 1-0 win over Jefferson and the Northwest 
League championship Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 When the two teams met Wednesday at Wilson, it was the Democrats who came out 
on top, 1-0. Jefferson's Gilberto Gomez goal ended the Mules' six-game unbeaten 
streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Jefferson (5-2-1, 1-1-1) and Wilson (5-1-2, 2-1) played back-to-back games for 
the league title. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Friday was the last day of the regular soccer season but, with 32 playoffs 
slots to fill, several area schools will see postseason action. 
</P>
<P>
 At the top of the list are the undefeated squads of Bell (8-0-1 in conference, 
4-0 in league) and Garfield (5-0-3, 4-0), both of the Southeastern Conference 
and champions of their respective leagues. Meanwhile in the Northern 
Conference, Belmont (5-1-2, 3-0) secured its Northeast League title and is tied 
with Wilson for the conference title. 
</P>
<P>
 The seeding meeting will take place Tuesday. Playoff matches begin Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 In Wednesday action:  
</P>
<P>
 Bell 1, South Gate 0 -- Eagle striker Maynor Alvarez scored on a free kick 
through a four-man wall in the 25th minute of the Southeastern Conference 
match.  
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt 1, Jordan 1 -- Bulldog Andrick Hernandez scored on a breakaway in 
the 15th minute to open the scoring. Five minutes later, Roughrider Alfonso 
Fuentes scored off a pass from David Medina for the equalizer. 
</P>
<P>
 Garfield 2, Huntington Park 1 -- The Bulldogs scored both goals within the 
first seven minutes of an Eastern League contest -- Romeo Cordova on a 
breakaway, followed by Dennis Valladares with a personal play. Jesus Cadenas 
scored the lone Spartan goal by beating the goalie with a hook shot to the 
upper-right corner before the first half ended. 
</P>
<P>
 Locke 2, Fremont 0 -- Ricardo Chavez scored in the 26th minute and Alberto 
Trujillo in the 38th on headers to put away the visiting Pathfinders in a 
Central League contest. 
</P>
<P>
 Belmont 7, Lincoln 0 -- Roberto Reyes scored twice in the second half on 
passes by Eric Hernandez to lift the Sentinels in a Northern Conference match. 
Hernandez and Salvador Gochez started the rout in the second and fourth minutes 
of the game. Jose Salmeron, Julio Vidrio and Nelson Moran each tallied once. 
</P>
<P>
 Fairfax 2, Manual Arts 1 -- Edwin Rivera scored his eighth goal of season and 
gave the Toilers a 1-0 lead five minutes into the Metro League match. But with 
five starters sidelined by injuries, the Toilers' hopes of qualifying for the 
playoffs were destroyed when the Lions came back with two goals. 
</P>
<P>
 In Friday games:  
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt 3, Jordan 1 -- Bulldog striker Salvador Siordia opened the scoring, 
but the Roughriders came back with goals by Alfredo Amado, Raul Lazaro and 
Alfonso Fuentes. With the victory, Roosevelt finished in second place in the 
Eastern League at 3-3-1, 2-2-1. Jordan ended its season at 0-6-2, 0-3-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Garfield 2, Huntington Park 0 -- Gerardo Gomez and Luis Garcia scored goals to 
secure the Bulldogs' Eastern League title. The Spartans finished 1-4-3, 1-3-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Locke 3, Fremont 1 -- The Saints foiled defending City Section champion 
Fremont's chances of advancing to the playoffs. E. Esperaza, Oscar Zendejas and 
Ricardo Chavez each tallied once to put away the Pathfinders in a Central 
League match. Locke finished 3-4-1, 2-3; Fremont was 1-3-3, 1-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell 4, South Gate 2 -- The Eagles were down 2-1 into the second half as 
strikers Osbaldo Macedo and Carlos Osorio each scored for the Rams. Angel 
Navarro, Oswaldo Williams, Hector Galdamez and Maynor Alvarez were Bell's 
scoring machine, cranking out the goals for the Central League win. The Rams 
finished 3-5-1, 2-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Belmont 2, Lincoln 1 -- Sentinel Jose Salmeron scored the winning goal in a 
Northern Conference match. 
</P>
