<TEXT>
<P>
 A side street of the information superhighway could be the typical 
neighborhood, with denizens schmoozing electronically and not worrying whether 
they're having a bad hair day. The technology for this exists today -- it's 
called the telephone -- but laptop computers with cellular modems, speedy fiber 
optics and interactive TV will take it to new levels.One question remains: If 
neighbors don't talk to each other now, will new gadgets force friendliness? 
